HTML Line Breaks

<p>This is<br>a paragraph<br>with line breaks.</p>
-------------------------------------------------------------------------
HTML Horizontal Rules
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<body>
  <h2>This is heading 2</h2>
  <p>This is some other text.</p>
  <hr>/////////////////////////////////////
  <h2>This is heading 2</h2>
  <p>This is some other text.</p>
</body>
</html>
-------------------------------------------------------------------------

The HTML <pre> Element -> for waiting proverb or poem

  <!DOCTYPE html>
  <html>
  <body>

  <p>The pre tag preserves both spaces and line breaks:</p>

  <pre>
     My Bonnie lies over the ocean.

     My Bonnie lies over the sea.

     My Bonnie lies over the ocean.

     Oh, bring back my Bonnie to me.
  </pre>

  </body>
  </html>
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
HTML Styles

Background Color

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<body style="background-color:powderblue;"> /////// Background Color

  <h1 style="color:blue;">This is a heading</h1> ////Text Color
  <p style="color:red;">This is a paragraph.</p> ////Text Color
  <h1 style="font-family:verdana;">This is a heading</h1> ////Fonts
  <p style="font-family:courier;">This is a paragraph.</p> /////Fonts
  <h1 style="text-align:center;">Centered Heading</h1> ////Text Alignment

</body>
</html>
-------------------------------------------------------------------------
Text Size
<h1 style="font-size:300%;">This is a heading</h1>
<p style="font-size:160%;">This is a paragraph.</p>

default size of all texts = 16px,
% -> will resize the element based on the parent
px -> will resize based on the pixels given

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<body>
<h1 style="font-size:16px;">This is a heading</h1>
<p style="font-size:200%;">This is a paragraph.</p>
<p style="font-size:32px;">This is a paragraph.</p>
<p >This is a  <a style="font-size:100%;">link</a> </p> /////////////////////// modify this to 200% -> equivalent to 32px since its parent is 16px
<p style="font-size:32px;">This is a  <a style="font-size:200%;">link</a> </p>
<p >This is a  <a style="font-size:100px;">link</a> </p>
</body>
</html>
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
HTML Text Formatting

HTML <sub> Element

  <!DOCTYPE html>
  <html>
  <body>

  <p><b>This text is bold.</b></p>
  <p><strong>This text is bold.</strong></p> ///////// browser will consider the content in this tag is more important
  <p><i>This text is italic.</i></p>
  <p><em>This text is emphasized</em></p> -> emphasized text
  <p><small>This is some smaller text.</small></p>
  <p>Do not forget to buy <mark>milk</mark> today.</p> -> highlighted text
  <p>My favorite color is <del>blue</del> red.</p> -> strike a line through
  <p>My favorite color is <del>blue</del> <ins>red</ins>.</p> -> text that has been inserted into a document. Browsers will usually underline inserted
  <p>This is <sub>subscripted</sub> text.</p>
  <p>This is <sup>superscripted</sup> text.</p>

  </body>
  </html>
